      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It is incredibly painful to feel that you are \"waiting for a permission slip to stop,\" especially when so many care about you deeply even if they cannot yet see you. Please reach out to a hospice bereavement counselor or a trusted friend whose voice you might hear from silence, for they might offer the one respect you did not lose: the respect that it is okay to not be okay. There is a life right in the feeling of your grief, even if it feels purposeless for now.",
